  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7<br /><br />Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel the <strong>potatoes</strong> (chop any large potatoes in half!)</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiling water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 minutes or until fork-tender</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over medium-high heat</p>\n<p>Pat the <strong>lamb rump</strong> dry and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> lamb rump</strong> and cook for 4-5 minutes, turning frequently, or until browned on all sides</p>\n<p>Once browned, transfer to a baking tray and set the pan and tray aside for later</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the potatoes are done, drain and leave them to steam dry</p>\n<p>Tip: For extra crispy potatoes, shake them around in a colander to fluff up the edges a little before roasting</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cooked potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with a generous drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and season generously with <strong>salt</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 35-40 minutes, turning halfway through, or until crispy</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>Knorr</strong> <strong>beef stock cube</strong> in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>. Return the pan to a medium heat</p>\n<p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1 minute, stirring frequently, or until a sandy paste forms</p>\n<p>Gradually mix in the <strong>beef stock, Henderson's Relish</strong> and <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> &amp; cook for 8-10 minutes or until a thick gravy remains</p>\n<p>Remove from the heat and reheat before serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put the <strong>lamb tray</strong> in the oven and cook for 23-25 minutes or until the lamb is slightly pink and blushing on the inside</p>\n<p>Once done, transfer to a plate and set aside to rest for at least 8-10 minutes</p>\n<p>Reserve the tray for step 7!</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>\n<p>Return the pot to a medium-low heat with a small knob of <strong>butter</strong></p>\n<p>Once melted, add the<strong> sliced leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 8-10 minutes or until softened</p>\n<p>Once softened, add the <strong>soft cheese</strong> and a splash of <strong>water</strong> and cook for 6-8 minutes further</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>purple sprouting broccoli</strong> to the reserved tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven and cook for 10-12 minutes or until tender</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, warm the <strong>creamed leek</strong> and <strong>redcurrant jus</strong> through over a low heat</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1574.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
